        content: "type: search_result\ntitle: Model Release Notes | OpenAI Help Center\nurl: \"https://help.openai.com/en/articles/9624314-model-release-notes\"\ndescription: \"Today, we've updated GPT-4o in ChatGPT. This version is better at incorporating uploaded files and updating memory with key parts of a conversation to make future interactions more helpful and relevant.\"\npage_age: 2 weeks ago\nprofile_name: OpenAI Help Center\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/-sx9cSUkCtgIg25EgH2jKoXXbkSGDmoEJ8QsozE_Dwg/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvYTU3MDYxM2Q3/OTA1OWM4MTBmZTY0/NTU3YjBiOTk4ZDA5/ZGZkYzdhMmQ2NmY3/OGZkZjdjMTZkMjhl/NThlYjUxZi9oZWxw/Lm9wZW5haS5jb20v\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/jAImN4w8EXYuhxWCfmutDGmdL5P4ukaIdsqqNztJVaE/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9oZWxw/Lm9wZW5haS5jb20v/b2ctaW1hZ2UucG5n\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://help.openai.com/og-image.png\"\nextra_snippets: \"Today, we've updated GPT-4o in ChatGPT. This version is better at incorporating uploaded files and updating memory with key parts of a conversation to make future interactions more helpful and relevant. \\\"Bug fixes and performance improvements” … we’ve introduced an update to GPT-4o that we’ve found, through experiment results and qualitative feedback, ChatGPT users tend to prefer.|We’re introducing GPT-4o mini, the most capable and cost-efficient small model available today. GPT-4o mini surpasses GPT-3.5 Turbo and other small models on academic benchmarks across both textual intelligence and multimodal reasoning and supports the same range of languages as GPT-4o.|You can read more about GPT-4o mini in the blog announcement.|previously announced, we have retired GPT-4o, GPT-4.1, GPT-4.1 mini, and OpenAI o4-mini from ChatGPT.\"\nhash: badf939bc215b9e6\nembed_ref: help.openai.com-D5I\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
